history.text: Hello.
Hi
Have you seen John Wick?
I saw it but I don't remember much.
No, I haven't.
It seems interesting. I like that Keanu Reeves is the main character.
I don't blame him for trying to get back at whoever killed his wife.
Yeah. He's a great actor, and a great person outside of film.

The plot is definitely different compared to other movies. It must be a good movie considering the rating on Rotten Tomatoes.
 They can be pretty harsh.
Do you recognize any of the actors/actresses besides Keanu Reeves?
I agree. That's a good rating.
No. I'm not big into action movies. I have Constantine playing right now with Keanu.
Sounds like some mob stuff is going on at this point.
Oh okay. Yeah, the movie does seem violent but I'm not sure if it's rated PG-13 or PG-18.
Probably rated r because of the violence.
I wonder why they killed his wife.
I agree. I don't know, It's also mentioned that someone killed his puppy, which was a gift from his wife.
Maybe because of his past connection being a hitman
Hmm... Losef stole John's car so maybe he was responsible for the killings too?
Sounds like typical scene.
Yeah, except that Losef is Viggo's son and John used to work for Viggo.
I think they always let the goodguy live.
Yeah, John lives after being captured by Viggo. It's sad that Viggo gives up his son's location in order to stay alive.
Some people don't have the best morals.
Viggo is a perfect example of that. Overall, I feel that it's a great plot and I think I would enjoy seeing it as there's more to come in the later movies.
I think there's a couple of the movies out
Seems John has a few reliable friends.
Probably since this one was made in 2014.
Yeah.
Sad ending, going back to the beach.
Yeah, he even got a new puppy as well. At least not everything was killed.
Yeah. Typical movie!
I have to agree. John and Winston are the only people that survive, which are the non-evil characters.

uid2response.feedback: I wanted to continue to speak about the movie but I guess after the time was up, the other User left. I felt that I was the only one actively involved in the conversation, making sure to include details from the document and tried to maintain flow of the conversation so it didn't die. The document is understandable although some of the key scenes were repeated. I don't think that without reading it, I would have wanted to watch John Wick now.
